title: Venus targets Singapore berth at HK Open
text: Photo: Andy Wong, AP Venus Williams of the United States reacts after missing a point to Ana Ivanovic of Serbia during the second round women's singles match of the China Open tennis tournament at the National Tennis Stadium in Beijing, Tuesday, Oct. 6, 2015. Venus Williams of the United States reacts after missing a point to... HONG KONG (AP) — Venus Williams will enter the last-chance saloon at the Hong Kong Open starting Monday as she eyes a berth in the season-ending WTA Finals in Singapore and a top-10 spot for the first time since 2011.
